org.openbel.framework.api
Class Namespaces

java.lang.Object
  org.openbel.framework.api.Namespaces

public class Namespaces
extends Object

Namespaces provides access to all namespaces supported by the BEL Framework instance.

The object is a singleton and is created/obtained by calling the synchronized static loadNamespaces(). Subsequent calls to loadNamespaces() will simply return the singleton instance without requiring a reload. This implies that namespaces cannot be reloaded without a JVM restart.

Author:
Anthony Bargnesi <abargnesi@selventa.com>

loadNamespaces

public static Namespaces loadNamespaces()
                                 throws IOException,
                                        ResourceDownloadError,
                                        XMLStreamException,
                                        BELDataMissingPropertyException,
                                        BELDataConversionException
Load namespaces supported by the BEL Framework instance. This synchrononized static method creates the singleton instance of Namespaces and loads the namespaces on first call.

Returns:
Namespaces singleton instance
Throws:
IOException - Thrown if an error occurred loading BEL Framework resources
ResourceDownloadError - Thrown if a download error occurred with a namespace resource location
XMLStreamException - Thrown if an xml error occurred parsing the resource index file
BELDataMissingPropertyException - Thrown if the namespace header definition is invalid
BELDataConversionException - Thrown if the namespace header definition is invalid
